  "text": "# Envoy Access Logging Infrastructure Audit\n\n## Summary\nAudited the access logging infrastructure in envoyproxy/envoy v1.31.2 and found 7 main access log sink implementations and 1 access log filter implementation, with corresponding proto definitions in envoyproxy/data-plane-api.\n\n## Access Log Sink Implementations\n\n### 1. File Access Logger\n**Repository:** envoyproxy/envoy\n**C++ Files:**\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/file/config.cc\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/file/config.h\n\n**Proto Definition:** envoy/extensions/access_loggers/file/v3/file.proto\n\n**Logging Support:** **STRUCTURED (JSON)**\n\n**Details:** The FileAccessLogFactory supports multiple logging formats:\n- Text format (deprecated) via `format` field\n- JSON format (deprecated) via `json_format` field using createJsonFormatter()\n- Typed JSON format (deprecated) via `typed_json_format` field\n- Current format via `log_format` field supporting SubstitutionFormatString\n\nThe implementation explicitly checks for `kJsonFormat` and `kTypedJsonFormat` cases and calls `Formatter::SubstitutionFormatStringUtils::createJsonFormatter()` for JSON support.\n\n### 2. Stream Access Logger (Stdout/Stderr)\n**Repository:** envoyproxy/envoy\n**C++ Files:**\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/stream/config.cc\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/stream/config.h\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/common/stream_access_log_common_impl.h\n\n**Proto Definitions:**\n- envoy/extensions/access_loggers/stream/v3/stream.proto (StdoutAccessLog, StderrAccessLog)\n\n**Logging Support:** **TEXT ONLY (Unstructured)**\n\n**Details:** Both stdout and stderr access loggers use createStreamAccessLogInstance<> template that only handles the `kLogFormat` case or defaults to text formatter. No JSON support in the proto definition or implementation.\n\n### 3. Fluentd Access Logger\n**Repository:** envoyproxy/envoy\n**C++ Files:**\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/fluentd/config.cc\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/fluentd/config.h\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/fluentd/fluentd_access_log_impl.h\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/fluentd/fluentd_access_log_impl.cc\n\n**Proto Definition:** envoy/extensions/access_loggers/fluentd/v3/fluentd.proto\n\n**Logging Support:** **STRUCTURED (JSON via MessagePack)**\n\n**Details:** The FluentdAccessLogFactory explicitly creates a JSON formatter by calling `Formatter::SubstitutionFormatStringUtils::createJsonFormatter(proto_config.record(), true, false, false, commands)` (line 65-67 in config.cc). The JSON is then converted to msgpack format for transmission to Fluentd. The proto defines a `record` field of type google.protobuf.Struct that represents the structured record to be sent.\n\n### 4. gRPC Access Logger (HTTP)\n**Repository:** envoyproxy/envoy\n**C++ Files:**\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/grpc/http_config.cc\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/grpc/http_config.h\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/grpc/http_grpc_access_log_impl.h\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/grpc/http_grpc_access_log_impl.cc\n\n**Proto Definition:** envoy/extensions/access_loggers/grpc/v3/als.proto (HttpGrpcAccessLogConfig)\n\n**Logging Support:** **STRUCTURED (Protocol Buffers)**\n\n**Details:** The HTTP gRPC logger creates HTTPAccessLogEntry protobuf messages (line 57 in http_grpc_access_log_impl.cc). It populates structured fields like common_properties, request, response, and protocol version. The data is sent as structured protocol buffer messages via gRPC, not JSON.\n\n### 5. gRPC Access Logger (TCP)\n**Repository:** envoyproxy/envoy\n**C++ Files:**\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/grpc/tcp_config.cc\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/grpc/tcp_config.h\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/grpc/tcp_grpc_access_log_impl.h\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/grpc/tcp_grpc_access_log_impl.cc\n\n**Proto Definition:** envoy/extensions/access_loggers/grpc/v3/als.proto (TcpGrpcAccessLogConfig)\n\n**Logging Support:** **STRUCTURED (Protocol Buffers)**\n\n**Details:** Similar to HTTP gRPC logger but uses TCPAccessLogEntry protobuf messages for TCP connections. Sends structured protobuf messages via gRPC.\n\n### 6. OpenTelemetry Access Logger\n**Repository:** envoyproxy/envoy\n**C++ Files:**\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/open_telemetry/config.cc\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/open_telemetry/config.h\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/open_telemetry/access_log_impl.h\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/open_telemetry/access_log_impl.cc\n\n**Proto Definition:** envoy/extensions/access_loggers/open_telemetry/v3/logs_service.proto\n\n**Logging Support:** **STRUCTURED (OpenTelemetry Protocol)**\n\n**Details:** The OpenTelemetry logger uses OpenTelemetry proto definitions (opentelemetry/proto/logs/v1/logs.pb.h, opentelemetry/proto/resource/v1/resource.pb.h). It supports structured attributes via opentelemetry.proto.common.v1.KeyValueList and body field. Can be configured with custom formatters via the formatters field in proto.\n\n### 7. WASM Access Logger\n**Repository:** envoyproxy/envoy\n**C++ Files:**\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/wasm/config.cc\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/wasm/config.h\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/wasm/wasm_access_log_impl.h\n\n**Proto Definition:** envoy/extensions/access_loggers/wasm/v3/wasm.proto\n\n**Logging Support:** **FLEXIBLE (Determined by WASM Module)**\n\n**Details:** The WASM access logger delegates logging implementation to a WASM module. The proto simply wraps envoy.extensions.wasm.v3.PluginConfig. Support for JSON or structured logging depends entirely on the WASM module implementation.\n\n## Access Log Filter Implementations\n\n### 1. CEL Expression Filter\n**Repository:** envoyproxy/envoy\n**C++ Files:**\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/filters/cel/config.cc\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/filters/cel/config.h\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/filters/cel/cel.h\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/filters/cel/cel.cc\n\n**Proto Definition:** envoy/extensions/access_loggers/filters/cel/v3/cel.proto\n\n**Purpose:** FILTER ONLY (Does not perform logging)\n\n**Details:** The CEL filter is an access logging filter that evaluates Common Expression Language expressions to determine whether an access log should be generated. It only filters; it does not handle logging format or structured/unstructured data.\n\n## Proto Definitions Without C++ Implementation\n\nThe following proto definitions exist in envoyproxy/data-plane-api but do not have corresponding C++ implementations in envoyproxy/envoy v1.31.2:\n\n1. **Stats Access Logger** (envoy/extensions/access_loggers/stats/v3/stats.proto)\n   - Configuration message: Config\n   - Purpose: Emits custom Envoy stats according to configuration\n   - Status: Proto defined but no C++ implementation found in source/extensions/access_loggers/\n\n2. **Process Rate Limit Filter** (envoy/extensions/access_loggers/filters/process_ratelimit/v3/process_ratelimit.proto)\n   - Configuration message: ProcessRateLimitFilter\n   - Purpose: Filters logs using global token buckets\n   - Status: Proto defined but no C++ implementation found in source/extensions/access_loggers/filters/\n\n3. **Dynamic Modules Access Logger** (envoy/extensions/access_loggers/dynamic_modules/v3/dynamic_modules.proto)\n   - Configuration message: DynamicModuleAccessLog\n   - Purpose: Loads shared object files via dlopen for custom logging\n   - Status: Proto defined but no C++ implementation found in source/extensions/access_loggers/\n\n## Core Access Log Infrastructure\n\n**Repository:** envoyproxy/envoy\n**C++ Files:**\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/common/access_log_base.h - Base class ImplBase for all sink implementations\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/common/file_access_log_impl.h - Shared file implementation for file-based sinks\n- source/common/access_log/access_log_impl.h - Core filter implementations (StatusCodeFilter, DurationFilter, HeaderFilter, etc.)\n\nThese provide foundational classes used by all access logger implementations.\n\n## Conclusion\n\nOut of 7 implemented access log sinks:\n- **2 support JSON:** File access logger and Fluentd access logger\n- **3 send structured but non-JSON:** gRPC (HTTP/TCP) and OpenTelemetry loggers use protocol buffers\n- **1 is text-only:** Stream (stdout/stderr) access logger\n- **1 is flexible:** WASM logger delegates to module\n\nThe audit identified all C++ sink and filter implementations, their corresponding proto definitions, and their logging format support capabilities."
}

